  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reduction of Ebola disease transmission in affected areas through the strengthening of SRH health services and protection against sexual exploitation and abuse in Katwa, Butembo, Biena and Musienene</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving sexual and reproductive health assistance and gender-based violence protection assistance to vulnerable communities in regions affected by, and those at risk of, Ebola. This UNFPA project procures hand-washing kits and infection prevention and control kits for 7 maternity wards; conducts refresher trainings for midwives on obstetric and neonatal care of suspected and confirmed Ebola patients; raises awareness about the infection prevention and control measures in local communities; supports the network for the prevention of sexual exploitation and abuse; and provides referral services for survivors of gender-based violence. The health component of the project provides life-saving assistance to 32,000 people, including 6,300 women, 6,100 men, 19,000 children, and 1,500 people with disabilities. The protection component of the project provides life-saving assistance to 20,000 people, including 4,200 women, 4,100 men, 11,700 children, and 1,000 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
